    p
      | Microsoft has launched a recent update to allow Microsoft Teams users to communicate with Skype for Business users. The new integration between the two apps will make it easier for users to migrate while still collaborating with colleagues that are still using Skype for Business. The new integration functionality will allow organizations to deploy Microsoft Teams to champions or specific departments prior to a full-scale deployment.
    p
      | Microsoft Teams users will see the Skype icon next to a person&rsquo;s name in the chat view. This icon indicates the user is still using Microsoft Skype for Business.
    p
      img(src='/assets/article/Teams-to-Skype/Microsoft-Teams-with-Skype-for.png', layout='intrinsic', attribution='CC courtesy of John L. Gruber on GitBit', alt='Microsoft Teams with Skype for Business Integration')
    p
      | Microsoft Teams will also warn your users in the Messages Header of a chat conversation that some functionality will not be possible between Microsoft Teams and Skype for Business Users. The loss of functionality is to be expected because Skype handles documents and other integrations differently. Since Microsoft is planning to retire Skype for Business I wouldn&rsquo;t anticipate a future update to make cross-app collaboration perfect.
    p
      img(src='/assets/article/Teams-to-Skype/Microsoft-Teams-warning-about-.png', layout='intrinsic', attribution='CC courtesy of John L. Gruber on GitBit', alt='Microsoft Teams warning about Skype features')
    p
      | The Skype icon will also be seen in Windows 10 notifications (that appear in the bottom right hand corner when Microsoft Teams is not your active app).
    p
      img(src='/assets/article/Teams-to-Skype/Windows-10-notification-with-M.png', layout='intrinsic', attribution='CC courtesy of John L. Gruber on GitBit', alt='Windows 10 notification with Microsoft Teams and Skype integration')
    p
      | The below screenshot is showing two separate users communicating across Skype for Business and Microsoft Teams. On the left, Adam Tucker, is using Skype for Business in OWA. On the right, Aaron Wells is using Microsoft Teams. Chat is fast and simple across the apps without any issues.
    p
      img(src='/assets/article/Teams-to-Skype/Microsoft-Teams-and-Skype-for-0.png', layout='intrinsic', attribution='CC courtesy of John L. Gruber on GitBit', alt='Microsoft Teams and Skype for Business chat integration')
  section
    h2 Microsoft Teams &ndash; Unified Presence
    table
      tr
        td
          p Feature ID
        td
          p 24191
      tr
        td
          p Description
        td
          p
            | This is one of the SfB messaging capabilities coming to Teams that supports unified presence between Teams and Skype for Business.
      tr
        td
          p Status
        td
          p Rolling Out
    blockquote
      | &ldquo;Presence states for users (i.e. available, busy or in a call) will now be aggregated between Teams and Skype for Business. This ensures that a user has a single presence state regardless of the app and the device they use. &nbsp;For this functionality, the underlying Skype for Business account that is connected to the Teams user needs to be hosted in Skype for Business online.&rdquo; &ndash; 
      a(href='https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/Microsoft-Teams-Blog/What-s-new-in-Microsoft-Teams-April-update/ba-p/179801') Microsoft
    p
      | Users in Microsoft Teams and Skype for Business can now see colleagues free/busy information across apps. The improved functionality will help users seamlessly migrate to Microsoft Teams and continue to work in a coordinated and professional manner.
    p
      | Upon testing, availability status updated flawlessly from Skype for Business to Microsoft Teams. I had some issues when the availability status did not update in Skype when a user made a change in Microsoft Teams. I&rsquo;m sure any issues are related to my test tenant or will be resolved shortly through a patch. Be sure to test availability in your tenant and discuss any issues with leadership and users.
    p
      img(src='/assets/article/Teams-to-Skype/Microsoft-Teams-and-Skype-for-1.png', layout='intrinsic', attribution='CC courtesy of John L. Gruber on GitBit', alt='Microsoft Teams and Skype for Business integrate presence status')
